Description: Unique index shared with tables "DCRreplanted141516gisfieldmap.csv", "LBSurvey23,csv", and "Dataset_for_final_analysis_fall23.csv"

Baseline surveys took place in 2014, 2015, and 2016. When a tree was observed in more than one of these years, I used the date and data from the most recent date. This goes for all baseline biometric data.

Should be 'BY', 'FY', 'MP', 'SY', 'Natural Area', or "UNKNOWN" (Backyard, Front Yard, Maintained Park, Side Yard). This column has many data entry errors. Could transpose with values from "SiteType_2023" (Tree has not changed location)

Should be 'INST', 'MFR', 'SFR-A', 'SFR-D' or "UNKNOWN" (Institution, Multi-Family Residence, Single Family Residence Attached, Single Family Residence Detached). This column has many data entry errors. Could transpose with values from "SiteType_2023" (Tree has not changed location)
'BY', 'FY', 'MP', 'SY', 'Natural Area', or "UNKNOWN" (Backyard, Front Yard, Maintained Park, Side Yard)
'INST', 'MFR', 'SFR-A', 'SFR-D' or "UNKNOWN" (Institution, Multi-Family Residence, Single Family Residence Attached, Single Family Residence Detached)
"1", "2", "3", or "4" I changed '0' and '5' to '' because we don' collect this data for dead trees
